    "body": "you can still do stuff like `app.all('*', middleware)`, but yeah generally I agree. It's very convenient the way it is and the only downside to having several routers is that settings and the other app prototype methods would not be available. This almost gets back to subapps acting as additional routers, there's no additional overhead in doing this and settings are inherited \n",
